[ROLE declarer][STAGE auction-end] Partner's 2NT was the Jacoby raise — four-card spade support with game values — and you are in 4\S needing ten tricks. Your side suit is dummy's \CA-Q-J-9-5 opposite your singleton 2: the ruffing-finesse layout again. Plan: cash the club ace, then push the jack through East. If East plays low, discard a loser from your hand — loser on loser — and the jack wins; if the king comes up, ruff it, and dummy's queen and nine are established. The club suit costs you nothing either way.

